Nicotiana rustica

   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Solanales:Solanaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names peasant's tobacco, Syrian tobacco, Aztec tobacco,
   makhorka, tabaco Azteca
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 7978

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 538-540 [LIG, DRA, USE]
   Kernick M 1961 pp 222-227 [PHO, KTMP, TEMP, RAIN, DRA, LIMITS]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Annual herb, growing for 90-120 days.
   COMMON NAMES
   Nicotine tobacco.
   FURTHER INF
   Nicotine tobacco probably orginated in Peru. In the tropics, it can be
   found at elevations between sea level and 1800 m.
   In advanced stage of growth the crop can be severely damaged by hail,
   heavy rain or strong winds. It can grow to a height of 0.5-1.5 m.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
